Payment Policy
All payments should be mailed in sufficient time to ensure receipt before the printed due date. Accounts which remain unpaid after the due
date will be subject to a 1.50% per month late charge on any past due balances. If you have had two dishonored checks within the
last 12 months payments must be made in cash, certified funds or credit card. Do not mail correspondence with your payment.
Delinquent Policy
Services will be scheduled for disconnect unless full payment on the previous balance is received in our office within 12 days of the Bill
Date printed on the front of this statement. After an order of disconnect has been dispatched, the total due plus additional service charges
including an administration fee must be paid in full before service can be reinstated. In addition, a deposit may be required on accounts
with a history of delinquency.
This statement constitutes formal notification that a lien may be placed against your property, your account may be referred to a third party
Collection Policy
collection agency, this balance may be reported to the three credit bureaus, and a collection fee may be added to your account if any
delinquent balance is not satisfied. (See Glendale City Code, Chapter 2, Article 1, Section 2.4)
Return Check Policy
If you receive a notice of a dishonored check, the amount of the check must be replaced immediately to avoid interruption of utility
services. Only cash or certified funds will be accepted as payment. A Non-Sufficient Check fee plus all applicable taxes will be
charged to your account.
Help Us Help You
Customers are reminded of their obligation to ensure their water meters can be read by City employees. Meters should be kept free
from overgrown plants and trees, rocks, dirt or other obstructions. Do not dispose of oil products or waste in your meter box. Damages
will be charged to your account. In addition, pets should be restricted to permit ready access to water meters.
